Sentencas: The effective oxygen conductivities in the zirconia networks of porous LSM-YSZ and LSM-SYSZ composites [i.e. La0.85Sr0.15MnO3-(Y2O3)(0.08)(ZrO2)(0.92) and La0.85Sr0.15MnO3-Sc2O3)(0.1)(Y2O3)(0.01)(ZrO2)(0.89), respectively] were evaluated by an AC impedance technique using specimens in which LSM was removed by hydrochloric acid leaching.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes

Sentencas: The oxygen conductivities of porous YSZ and SYSZ alone followed a Koh-Fortini relationship.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes

Sentencas: LSM-containing zirconia network conductivities were additionally decreased by the presence of the LSM.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes

Sentencas: Grain boundary resistances were not measurably increased.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes

Sentencas: Network constriction resistances were estimated to have a minor effect for well-formed networks.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes

Sentencas: The significant microstructural differences of the YSZ and SYSZ, when formed with and without LSM, then indicate that the significant decrease in network effective ion conductivity is likely to be attributable to an increase in network interruptions and anomalously high constriction resistances resulting from differential densification promoted by the LSM.
Titulo: Ionic conductivity of stabilized zirconia networks in composite SOFC electrodes
